&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About SpringWorks Therapeutics:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SpringWorks Therapeutics, a healthcare company of Merck KGaA, Darmstadt, Germany, is a commercial-stage biopharmaceutical company dedicated to improving the lives of patients with rare tumors.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;We developed and are commercializing the first and only FDA and EC approved medicine for adults with desmoid tumors and the first and only FDA and EC approved medicine for both adults and children with neurofibromatosis type 1 associated plexiform neurofibromas (NF1-PN).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;At SpringWorks, we are committed to finding answers people with rare tumors need. We thrive in an atmosphere of passion and tenacity, fueled by the excitement of the possibilities science may unlock and driven to work with urgency because of the importance of our work. We value authenticity because diverse backgrounds, cultures, styles and abilities can only help us find the answers that people with rare tumors are looking for&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Your Role:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director of Commercial Operations- Market Access holds accountability for all field operations to secure operational efficiency and customer effectiveness for the Market Access Team as well as the Field Access Management Team . The Director of Commercial Operations- Market Access serves as an essential business partner to the entire Market Access team including the Field Access Managers, &amp;nbsp;a peer to the Field Training Director and works proactively to ensure seamless, service-oriented, and strategic operations across all Commercial functions. This role is a key business partner for Marketing, Sales Operations, Data &amp;amp; Analytics, Marketing Operations, Finance, and Compliance.&amp;nbsp; This role acts as the liaison to HQ functions on behalf of Market Access roles, including but not limited to HR, Legal, IT, and Finance, and Training. It reports directly to Executive Director, Commercial Operations. The successful candidate is deeply passionate about data analytics, enabling the team to execute positive customer experiences and confidently couples strategic thinking, operational planning and teamwork to deliver on desired outcomes. This is a hands-on position that requires candidates to serve in both a strategic, analytical and tactical capacity to be able to influence through actions and results rather than authority. Success in this role means anticipating leadership needs across functions, driving initiatives with autonomy, and continuing to look for ways to deliver operational impact for your stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
